options.label: nlm-indomethacin-plot
options.fig.cap: Concentration of Indomethacin in a single subject with the estimated nonlinear model overlayed.

options.label: fig-nlm-indometh-resids
options.fig.cap: Plot of the residuals against the predicted values for data from a study of the pharmacokinetics of Indothemacin.
options.fig.alt: The left panel is a scatterplot of the residuals against predicted values; the right panel is a scatterplot of the absolute residuals against the predicted values.

options.label: fig-nlm-indomethacin-resample-plot
options.fig.cap: Potential bootstrap resample of the Indomethacin data resulting from case resampling. In this resample, the primary curvature present in the original data is lost.

options.label: fig-nlm-indometh-sampdistns-plot
options.fig.cap: Comparison of two models for the sampling distribution of a parameter in the bi-exponential model fit to data examining the pharmacokinetics of Indomethacin.  The left panel is the model for the sampling distribution based on large sample theory when we assume the variance is constant; the right panel is the model for the sampling distribution based on a wild bootstrap.
options.fig.alt: Two density plots; the left panel is shifted to the left compared to the right panel.
